==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Undecylic
<hw>Un`de*cyl"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Related to, derived from, or containing, the undecyl radical;
specifically, designating that member of the fatty acids which
corresponds to undecane, and is obtained as a white crystalline
substance, <chform>C10H21.CO2H</chform>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

